WEBVTT

00:01.187 --> 00:04.511
<font color=#FF00FF>*LIFE IN PIECES*</font>
<font color=#00FF00>Season 04 Episode 03</font>

00:05.137 --> 00:07.703
<font color=#FFFF00>Story One:
Broken Mom-Mom</font>

00:08.437 --> 00:10.125
How's your knee
feeling, Joanie?

00:10.213 --> 00:13.129
The doc seemed pretty confident
when he said one week.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.319
But, y-you know,
you got to get out of bed,

00:15.406 --> 00:17.017
put some weight on it. Here.

00:17.104 --> 00:20.542
No. I don't trust that doctor.
He wore jeans.

00:20.629 --> 00:22.283
Hmm.

00:22.370 --> 00:24.732
Wait, don't go. Don't go.

00:24.950 --> 00:27.487
Oh, I'm so bored.

00:27.575 --> 00:29.519
Well, geez,
I'd love to hang out,

00:29.607 --> 00:32.206
but, uh, I got an appointment
I cannot break.

00:32.380 --> 00:33.520
With whom?

00:33.638 --> 00:35.841
Whoever they pair me up with.

00:42.472 --> 00:44.529
Hey, Mom-Mom.

00:44.617 --> 00:48.779
Sophia. You came to see
the Mom-Mom you love.

00:48.867 --> 00:50.390
Oh, I'm just delivering
a sandwich.

00:50.478 --> 00:55.005
No, no, no. You want to talk
and tell me all your problems.

00:55.333 --> 00:58.362
Perhaps, uh, you're feeling
invisible at school?

00:58.449 --> 01:01.878
No, school's great. I just got
to name our new mascot,

01:01.966 --> 01:04.888
Inclusive the Rainbow.Oh.

01:05.281 --> 01:08.081
I guess I did just get kind of
annoyed with my mom, though.

01:08.169 --> 01:11.450
Oh, wonderful. Tell me, honey.
Sit down, tell me.

01:11.549 --> 01:13.036
I wanted her to play a game,

01:13.124 --> 01:16.448
but she said she's too exhausted
from taking care of you

01:16.536 --> 01:18.434
and listening to all
your complaints and demands.

01:18.521 --> 01:19.542
Hmm. Well, you know,

01:19.630 --> 01:21.044
I gave her 40 years,

01:21.132 --> 01:22.960
and she walked some toast
across the street,

01:23.048 --> 01:24.005
so I guess we're even.

01:24.093 --> 01:26.833
She said you owe her.
Later.

01:27.168 --> 01:29.964
Whoa, honey,
don't leave me, please.

01:30.052 --> 01:31.982
You know, I can play
that game with you.

01:32.070 --> 01:33.279
Really?

01:34.968 --> 01:37.797
I didn't know there was a truth
or dare version of this game.

01:38.064 --> 01:40.378
There's also an X-rated version
of Monopoly.

01:40.466 --> 01:42.620
I found it
in Mom and Dad's closet.

01:42.708 --> 01:44.825
Instead of a car,
there were handcuffs.

01:44.913 --> 01:46.318
Instead of a thimble,
there was some...

01:46.405 --> 01:48.786
Um, no, honey.
I-I understand what you mean.

01:48.874 --> 01:52.026
Okay, so, "Dare one player
to run around the room."

01:52.114 --> 01:53.286
I dare you.

01:53.374 --> 01:56.458
Run? Get a grip.
I can't even walk.

01:56.546 --> 01:58.333
Then I dare you
to prank call someone.

01:58.421 --> 01:59.640
I don't know, not with me.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.802
I'm not funny that way.

02:02.536 --> 02:05.005
Seymour Butts doesn't live here.

02:05.093 --> 02:06.482
Okay? Who is this?

02:06.584 --> 02:08.566
You know what?
You are a little piece of...

02:08.654 --> 02:10.622
Oh, mercy.

02:10.723 --> 02:12.567
Oh, that was upsetting.

02:12.654 --> 02:13.974
I'm gonna go get
some more games.

02:14.062 --> 02:14.974
What?

02:15.062 --> 02:18.482
I love having a broken Mom-Mom
who can't leave her bed.

02:21.685 --> 02:23.018
One...

02:23.106 --> 02:24.161
two...

02:24.249 --> 02:26.568
Oh, phew.

02:28.865 --> 02:32.021
Four?
That's too many.

02:35.882 --> 02:36.904
Can we get out yet?

02:36.992 --> 02:38.635
I'm a little starved for air.

02:38.723 --> 02:41.425
We all are.
It's a nuclear holocaust.

02:41.513 --> 02:43.193
Mm, right. But I...

02:43.396 --> 02:44.950
Are you crazy?

02:45.038 --> 02:47.297
Mom-Mom,
it isn't safe.

02:47.384 --> 02:49.513
Get back in the fort now.

02:49.746 --> 02:51.387
Wake up, Mom-Mom.

02:51.825 --> 02:53.052
What's happening?

02:53.140 --> 02:54.997
I'm the wicked stepmother.

02:55.305 --> 02:57.351
You're gonna have
to eat your way out.

02:57.761 --> 02:59.482
- Hey, Mom.
- Ooh.

02:59.570 --> 03:02.130
A visitor.
I'm up here!

03:02.218 --> 03:04.394
Shh. You need your rest.

03:04.560 --> 03:07.317
- I'll take care of it.
- Honey?

03:08.616 --> 03:11.529
Oh! Hey, uh, Soph.
Th-This is for Mom-Mom.

03:11.713 --> 03:13.654
Oh, okay.
She's not taking

03:13.742 --> 03:15.302
visitors right now.
She's resting.

03:15.390 --> 03:17.935
Uh, somebody's out there.
I can hear you.

03:18.052 --> 03:19.607
Hello?

03:22.220 --> 03:24.222
Did you call Uncle Greg?

03:24.693 --> 03:26.641
No, I didn't.

03:26.904 --> 03:28.643
I'll just hold onto this.

03:28.730 --> 03:30.688
Anything you need,
I'll get you.

03:30.776 --> 03:32.806
Well, would you untie me,
please?

03:32.894 --> 03:37.749
No. I've got other
plans for you.

03:37.837 --> 03:39.456
We're gonna smash geodes.

03:39.654 --> 03:43.050
No, we're not.
I have had enough of this.

03:43.144 --> 03:45.573
Just untie me!

03:46.433 --> 03:49.120
I thought we were
having fun together.

03:50.214 --> 03:51.847
Oh, darling.

03:52.330 --> 03:54.292
I didn't want to do that.

03:54.480 --> 03:55.862
I'm so sorry.

03:55.995 --> 04:00.105
You've been just so...
you've been so wonderful to me.

04:00.347 --> 04:02.677
Honey, I'm so sorry.

04:02.764 --> 04:04.011
I'll tell you what.

04:04.099 --> 04:05.548
You know, you go home,

04:05.636 --> 04:08.813
and you just get us
some more games, okay?

04:08.971 --> 04:10.308
I've got a really fun one

04:10.396 --> 04:13.181
where the loser gets their
fingers electrocuted.

04:13.501 --> 04:14.720
Brilliant.

